The paper deals with lower bounds for computation of the Fourier transform in a linear circuit model, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of matrix entropy suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). The layered linear circuit model and the use of potential functions suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the use of unitary gates suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
